<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1615]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1446,1471]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male of this new species is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zavattari" authorityName="Zavattari" box="[913,1264,1446,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoozana">
<emphasis box="[913,1131,1446,1470]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">Hemutilla hoozana</emphasis>
(Zavattari)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by having mandible beneath basally strongly widened (slightly rounded in 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1131,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoozana">
<emphasis box="[997,1131,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">H. hoozana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the legs and metasomal segment 
<number box="[251,265,1519,1543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" value="1.0">1</number>
ferruginous-red (black in 
<taxonomicName box="[559,688,1518,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Hemutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoozana">
<emphasis box="[559,688,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">H. hoozana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,258,1615]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1554,1579]" pageId="10" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name consists of a Latin adjective meaning &quot;ferruginous&quot; and a Latin noun pes, meaning &quot;leg&quot; with reference to the ferruginous legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
